commit.message: Add an example to --time-scale documentation
Updated ChangeLog

Run the autoupdate to drop the obsolete macros in configure.ac

Both AC_HAVE_LIBRARY and AC_HELP_STRING are obsolete, so update
the prereq on the autoconf tools to use and replace the macros

Update boost and gl macros from autoconf archive for non-GNU

Mac OS X Montery with brew couldn't get find the Boost System,
GL, and GLU libs. Adding the updated macros resolve the configure
errors.

Note that Wayland support is experimental

High DPI behaviour not tested
Fix building when GLEW_ERROR_NO_GLX_DISPLAY not defined
Added support for running on Wayland.
Fixed tense.
Reformat text.
Fixed hovering over end of slider stopping time advancing.

Add --high-dpi option

Requesting High DPI on MacOS may cause the pixel resolution to be doubled.

If a resolution has been specified this may not be appropriate
E.g. if you are recording a video at a specific resolution

Can override by supplying --high-dpi option.

Change threshold for doubling default font-scale to height of 1600

E.g. 2560x1600 will get a font-scale of 2.
Fixed various bugs with Retina diplays on MacOS.
Fixed slider timestamp font not being affected by font_scale.
Update ChangeLog
Allow Gource to render at native resolution on High DPI displays
Reload shaders with F5 to make them easier to debug
Allow caption timestamp to be be an ISO 8601 format string
Resaved png images
Add test-driver used by make check

Add publisher to registry entries

It is best practice to have the publisher filled in the Add/Remove Programs table. This PR adds the registry key for that
Windows build fixes

Fixed uninitialized value warning in version parsing

Removed a work around for a very old git log version
Change regular expression library to PCRE2

Allow timestamp in custom log to be a string

Support parsing ISO 8601 timestamps

Added tests for timestamp parsing
Fix array delete mismatch
Updated UTF8-CPP to 3.1.2
Change README to markdown.
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/pr/249'
